{"lemma":"أَصِيلٌ","slug":"أَصِيلٌ","root":"#.ص.ل","root_slug":"_-ص-ل","root_link":"/words/roots/_-ص-ل","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"أَصِيل","root":"أصل","pos":"N","occurrence_count":7},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["adj","name"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":4},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n886"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A3%D9%8E%D8%B5%D9%90%D9%8A%D9%84%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"original, genuine, deep-rooted"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"noble"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"purebred (horses, etc)"},{"pos":"name","gloss":"a male given name, Asil"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"فَعِيل (faʕīl)-type stative-verb derived from the active participle from the verb أَصُلَ (ʔaṣula). Cognate with Hebrew אָצִיל (atsíl)."},"ipa":["/ʔa.sˤiːl/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n886","headword_ar":"اَصِيلٌ","root":"ASl","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Having root,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a foundation;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and consequently,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having rootedness, fixedness, immobility, stability,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"permanence; rooted, fixed, immoveable, stable,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"permanent"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~a Aln~axola fiY A^aroDinaA laA^aSiylN","text_ar":"اـِنَّ النَّخْلَ فِى اَرْضِنَا لَاَصِيلٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Verily the palm-trees in our land remain permanently, not perishing."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, TA.) ―         -b2-  A man"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aSol","text_ar":"اَصْل"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K, TA,) i. e.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lincage,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pedigree:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"established in his"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aSol","text_ar":"اَصْل"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Abu-l-BaKà, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"noble,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"generous."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) ―         -b3-  A man"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"firm of judgment, and intelligent."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K.* [Accord. to the copies of the latter, the signification is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaAqibN vaAbitu Alr~aA^oYi","text_ar":"عَاقِبٌ ثَابِتُ الرَّاْىِ"},{"kind":"text","text":": but I think that the right reading of the first word is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaAqilN","text_ar":"عَاقِلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as in the M, in which this word occupies the last place in the explanation.]) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aSiylu Alr~aA^oYi","text_ar":"اَصِيلُ الرَّاْىِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"A man"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"firm,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sound, of judgment."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raA^oYN A^aSiylN","text_ar":"رَاْىٌ اَصِيلٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Judgment having"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aSol","text_ar":"اَصْل"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"firmness"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (M.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"majodN A^aSiylN","text_ar":"مَجْدٌ اَصِيلٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Glory, honour, dignity,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"nobility, having a firm root"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"foundation."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ar~N A^aSiylN","text_ar":"شَرٌّ اَصِيلٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Vehement evil"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mischief."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ibn-'Abbád.)       -A2-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aSilN","text_ar":"اَصِلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in two places. ―         -b2-  [Hence, app.,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^aSiylu","text_ar":"الاَصِيلُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Destruction:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"death:"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also, in both senses, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^aSiylapu","text_ar":"الاَصِيلَةُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.)       -A3-  [The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"evening;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or] i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ea$iY~N","text_ar":"عَشِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (M, K, Msb, TA;) i. e. (Msb, TA) the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"time from the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSor","text_ar":"عَصْر"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from the prayer of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ESr","text_ar":"عصر"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to sunset;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Sudot;, Msb, TA;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aSiylapN","text_ar":"اَصِيلَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (R, TA:) the pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uSulN","text_ar":"اُصُلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, R, Msb, K,) or ↓ this is a sing., (TA,) or it may be a sing., (M,) for it is used as such, (M, TA,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uSolaAnN","text_ar":"اُصْلَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, K,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A=SaAlN","text_ar":"ا=صَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, Sgh, K,) [a pl. of pauc.,] or, accord. to Es- Saláh Es-Safadee, this is a pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uSulN","text_ar":"اُصُلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", the sing., not the pl., (TA,) or it is pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uSulN","text_ar":"اُصُلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Zj, M,) which may be a pl. or a sing., (M,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aSaAy^ilu","text_ar":"اَصَايِلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, K,) as though pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aSiylapN","text_ar":"اَصِيلَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,) or it is pl. of this last word. (R, TA.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laqiytuhu A^aSiylFA","text_ar":"لَقِيتُهُ اَصِيلًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uSulFA","text_ar":"اُصُلًا","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e. ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I met him in the evening,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ea$iy~FA","text_ar":"عَشِيًّا"},{"kind":"text","text":". (A, TA.) From the pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uSolaAnu","text_ar":"اُصْلَانُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is formed the dim. ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uSayolaAnN","text_ar":"اُصَيْلَانٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, K,) which is extr., (M, K,) because the dim. of a pl. is [regularly] formed only from a pl. of pauc., which"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ASlAn","text_ar":"اصلان"},{"kind":"text","text":"is not; or, if"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ASlAn","text_ar":"اصلان"},{"kind":"text","text":"be a sing., like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rum~aAnN","text_ar":"رُمَّانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qurobaAnN","text_ar":"قُرْبَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", this"},{"kind":"page_break","n":66},{"kind":"text","text":"dim. is regular: (M:) sometimes, (K,) one says also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uSayolaAlN","text_ar":"اُصَيْلَالٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, K,) substituting"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"l","text_ar":"ل"},{"kind":"text","text":"for the [final]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"n","text_ar":"ن"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M.*) You say, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laqiytuhu A^uSayolaAnFA","text_ar":"لَقِيتُهُ اُصَيْلَانًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uSayolaAlFA","text_ar":"اُصَيْلَالًا","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning, as above,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ea$iy~FA","text_ar":"عَشِيًّا"},{"kind":"text","text":": (A, TA:) and Lh mentions ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lqyth A^uSay~aAlFA","text_ar":"لقيته اُصَيَّالًا","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (So in two copies of the S.)"}],"source_refs":["K","TA","Msb","S","R","M","Sgh","Zj","A"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}